        <tr> 
         <td class="oddRowEvenCol"> <h3>Welcome to the Postgraduate Institute of Medicine Library Repository...</h3><p>The PGIM is the only institute in Sri Lanka that is responsible for the specialist training of Medical doctors. It is a national institute that is attached to the University of Colombo. It is internationally recognised and several of its training programmes have 'equivalence' recognition by the Royal Colleges of the UK.</p><p>The PGIM is governed by a Board of Management. The academic programmes are planned and executed by 21 Boards of Study. Our vision is "to be a financially and administratively independent institute, internationally recognized as an center of excellence, producing specialists of high professional standards, to meet health needs of the country and contribute to regional and world health in a responsive manner..".</p><p>Moving a step further, we now present you our new information service, "<span style="color:#cc6600;font-weight:bold;">PGIM Library Repository (PGIM LR)</span>" enabling equitable access to intellectual assets of the PGIM. Most items in our Repository are freely accessible up to original full-text materials. In addition our Repository also features photo and video archives of the PGIM.</p><p>If you have information materials that you would like to share with your colleagues, please contact PGIM Library Repository Team. We will be willing to incorporate them into our Repository.</p><br><p>PGIM Library RepositoryTeam</p> </td> 
        </tr> 
